<h2>
    Fishing Regulations and Licensing
</h2>
<h3>
    Oregon Fishing License Requirements
</h3>
<p>
    You’ll need an Oregon angling license with a <strong>Combined Angling Tag</strong> to fish for salmon. These are available online or at local sporting goods stores.
</p>
<h3>
   Daily Limits and Gear Restrictions
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Limits:</strong> Usually 2 salmon per day (check seasonal updates).
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Gear:</strong> Barbless hooks required in many locations.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Check daily updates</strong> on the Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife (ODFW) website.
    </li>
</ul>
